/* cGridToCJGridBase.pkg

 Abstract base class for CJ grid conversion worker classes.
 Shared by:
   cDbGridTocDbCJGrid  (data-aware:     DbGrid/cLangDbGrid -> cDbCJGrid)
   cGridToCJGrid       (non-data-aware: Grid               -> cCJGrid)

 This class provides all transformation logic that operates at the cCJGrid level --
 property translation, legacy property removal, method renaming, Entry_Display
 commenting, and legacy-only method commenting.  It does NOT know about column
 sub-objects or Begin_Row / Entry_Item constructs; those are added by subclasses
 through three override hooks:

   OnGridStarted sGridIndent
       Called once when a matching grid declaration is detected.
       Subclasses reset their per-grid state here.

   OnHandleGridLine sLine sTrimLine sLower asOutput ByRef sGridIndent bSkip ByRef
       Called for every source line at nesting level 1 (direct grid content),
       before the base class's own property/method dispatch.
       Set bSkip True to consume the line; leave False to let base processing run.
       The subclass may emit content into asOutput before returning.

   OnBeforeGridEndObject asOutput ByRef sGridIndent
       Called once just before the grid's own End_Object is emitted.
       Subclasses flush any buffered column objects here.

 Shared transformations applied to each grid object found:
   - "Object X is a <OldGridClass>"    ->  "Object X is a <NewGridClass>"
   - Commented out: Set Main_File (hints which DDO to wire up)
   - Removed: Set Wrap_State, Set psColumnsID, Set Visible_State, Set Dynamic_Update_State
   - Removed: Define <constant> N (column index constants)
   - Removed: Set Child_Table_State, Set Item_Limit, Set Base_Item,
              Set pbComboNavigation, Set Move_Value_Out_State,
              Set Auto_Export_State, Set Auto_Index_State, Set Auto_Column_State
   - Commented out: Entry_Display procedure block
   - Translated: Set peResizeColumn        -> Set pbAllowColumnResize
   - Translated: Set Prompt_Button_Mode    -> Set pbHeaderPrompts
   - Translated: Set Allow_Top_Add_State   -> Set pbAllowAppendRow
   - Translated: Set Allow_Bottom_Add_State-> Set pbAllowAppendRow
   - Translated: Set Allow_Insert_Add_State-> Set pbAllowInsertRow
   - Translated: Set Auto_Save_State       -> Set pbAutoSave
   - Translated: Set Auto_Regenerate_State -> Set pbAutoRegenerate
   - Translated: Set No_Create_State       -> Set pbAllowAppendRow + Set pbAllowInsertRow (inverted)
   - Translated: Set No_Delete_State       -> Set pbAllowDeleteRow (inverted)
   - Translated: Set Read_Only_State       -> Set pbReadOnly
   - Translated: Set Header_Visible_State  -> Set pbShowHeader
   - Translated: Set Resize_Column_State   -> Set pbAllowColumnResize
   - Translated: Set Highlight_Row_State   -> Set pbShowRowFocus
   - Translated: Set Gridline_Mode         -> Set peHorizontalGridStyle / peVerticalGridStyle
   - Translated: Set CurrentRowColor       -> Set piHighlightBackColor
   - Translated: Set CurrentRowTextColor   -> Set piHighlightForeColor
   - Translated: Set CurrentCellColor      -> Set piFocusCellBackColor
   - Translated: Set CurrentCellTextColor  -> Set piFocusCellForeColor

 Method override handling (Procedure/Function blocks inside the grid body):
   - Renamed:    Goto_Top_Row    -> MoveToFirstRow   (Forward Send/Get also renamed)
   - Renamed:    Goto_Bottom_Row -> MoveToLastRow     (Forward Send/Get also renamed)
   - Renamed:    Up_Row          -> MoveUpRow         (Forward Send/Get also renamed)
   - Renamed:    Down_Row        -> MoveDownRow       (Forward Send/Get also renamed)
   - Converted: Mouse_Click   Integer iWin Integer iPos  ->  Procedure OnRowDoubleClick Integer iRow Integer iCol
                (declaration replaced; Forward Send rewritten; old param names substituted in body)
   - Converted: Mouse_Down2  Integer iWin Integer iPos  ->  Procedure OnRowRightClick  Integer iRow Integer iCol
                (declaration replaced; Forward Send rewritten; old param names substituted in body)
   - Commented out with TODO hint: Fill_List, Refresh_Page, Request_New_Index, Move_to_Column
   - Commented out (no equivalent): Beginning_of_Data, End_of_Data, CheckBox_Item,
     Reorder_List, Auto_Reorder_List, Scroll, Clear_Current_Record, Col_Index, Display,
     DoCheckDisplayableRows, DoToggleColumnOrdering, Find_Current_Buffer, Find_Init,
     Find_Record, Find_RowId, ReadByRowId, Read_By_Recnum, ServerOrderingOverride,
     Activate_Column, Activate_Item, DoAdjustGridWidths, Column_Combo_*,
     DoMakeColumnVisible, Request_Superfind, SuperFind, SuperFind_Next,
     SuperFind_Previous, Validate_Items, Exec_Entry, Exec_Exit, Exec_Validate,
     Change_Row_Color (-> consider OnSetRowColor)
   - All other procedure/function overrides are preserved unchanged.

 All other content (other Set properties, nested objects, etc.) is preserved unchanged.

 The sParameter passed to TransformFiles must be a comma-separated string of 2 or 3
 class names:  "OldGridClass,NewGridClass[,NewColumnClass]"
 If sParameter is empty, the old class is detected by the subclass IsGridDeclaration
 override, and the default class names set in the subclass constructor are used.
*/

Use vWin32fh.pkg
Use RefactorConstants.h.pkg
Use WsGlobalFunctions.pkg
Use GlobalFunctionsProcedures.pkg
Use cEncodingHelpers.pkg

#IFNDEF phoEditorRefactored
    Register_Function phoEditorRefactored Returns Handle
#ENDIF

Class cGridToCJGridBase is a cObject

    Procedure Construct_Object
        Forward Send Construct_Object
        Property String[]  pasSource
        Property String    psFileName          ""
        Property Integer   piChangedFiles       0
        Property Integer   piChangedGrids       0
        // Class name parameters (set by ParseAndSetParameter).
        // psLegacyGridClass: "" means pattern-based detection (defined by subclass).
        Property String    psLegacyGridClass   "DbGrid"
        Property String    psTargetGridClass   "cCJGrid"
        Property String    psTargetColumnClass "cCJGridColumn"
        // Per-grid state: translatable Entry_Display properties collected during
        // grid pre-scan, flushed by FlushEntryDisplayExtracted before column objects.
        Property String[]  pasEntryDisplayExtracted
        Property Boolean   pbEntryDisplayFlushed  False
        Property Boolean   pbLastFileWasUtf8      False
    End_Procedure

    // *** File I/O ***

    // Reads a source file using the byte-safe helpers. Auto-detects UTF-8 BOM
    // and stores the result in pbLastFileWasUtf8 for use by WriteFile.
    Procedure ReadFile String sFileName
        String[] asSource
        Set psFileName        to sFileName
        Set pbLastFileWasUtf8 to (FileHasBOM(sFileName))
        Move (ReadEncodedFileAsStringArray(sFileName)) to asSource
        Set pasSource to asSource
    End_Procedure

    // Writes the source array back to disk using the byte-safe helpers,
    // preserving the encoding (UTF-8 BOM or OEM/CP850) detected by ReadFile.
    Procedure WriteFile
        String   sFileName
        String[] asSource
        Boolean  bOK bIsUtf8

        Get psFileName        to sFileName
        Get pasSource         to asSource
        Get pbLastFileWasUtf8 to bIsUtf8
        Move (WriteEncodedFileFromStringArray(asSource, sFileName, CS_CRLF, bIsUtf8)) to bOK
        If (bOK = False) Begin
            Error DFERR_PROGRAM ("Write failed:" * sFileName * "(cGridToCJGridBase WriteFile)")
        End
    End_Procedure

    // *** Parameter parsing ***

    // Parses sParameter ("OldClass,NewGridClass[,NewColumnClass]") and sets the
    // three class name properties.
    // - Empty sParameter: use defaults set by the subclass constructor.
    // - 2 parts: exact old-class match and new grid class; column stays as-is.
    // - 3 parts: all three specified.
    // Returns False (and sets an Error) when sParameter is invalid.
    Function ParseAndSetParameter String sParameter Returns Boolean
        String[]  asParts
        String    sOld sNewGrid sNewCol
        Integer   iParts

        // Empty -> leave defaults from constructor unchanged.
        If (sParameter = "") Begin
            Set psLegacyGridClass to ""
            Function_Return True
        End

        Move (StrSplitToArray(sParameter, ",")) to asParts
        Move (SizeOfArray(asParts)) to iParts

        If (iParts < 2 or iParts > 3) Begin
            Error DFERR_PROGRAM ('RefactorGridToCJGrid: sParameter must be "OldGridClass,NewGridClass[,NewColumnClass]".')
            Function_Return False
        End

        Move (Trim(asParts[0])) to sOld
        Move (Trim(asParts[1])) to sNewGrid

        If (sOld = "" or sNewGrid = "") Begin
            Error DFERR_PROGRAM ("RefactorGridToCJGrid: OldGridClass and NewGridClass must not be empty.")
            Function_Return False
        End

        If (iParts = 3) Begin
            Move (Trim(asParts[2])) to sNewCol
        End
        If (sNewCol <> "") Begin
            Set psTargetColumnClass to sNewCol
        End

        // Store old class name as lowercase for case-insensitive comparison.
        Set psLegacyGridClass to (Lowercase(sOld))
        Set psTargetGridClass to sNewGrid
        Function_Return True
    End_Function

    // *** Detection helpers ***

    // Override in subclasses to detect the specific legacy grid class.
    // When psLegacyGridClass is set, should do an exact (case-insensitive) match.
    // When psLegacyGridClass is empty, should fall back to a pattern check.
    // Base implementation always returns False.
    Function IsGridDeclaration String sTrimLower Returns Boolean
        Function_Return False
    End_Function

    // Returns True when sTrimLower is an Object declaration of any kind.
    Function IsObjectDeclaration String sTrimLower Returns Boolean
        Function_Return (Pos("object ", sTrimLower) = 1 and Pos(" is a ", sTrimLower) <> 0)
    End_Function

    // Returns True when sTrimLower is an Entry_Display procedure start.
    Function IsEntryDisplayProcedure String sTrimLower Returns Boolean
        Function_Return (Pos("procedure ", sTrimLower) = 1 and Pos("entry_display", sTrimLower) <> 0)
    End_Function

    // Returns True when sTrimLower is a legacy grid-only Set property to remove.
    Function IsLegacyGridProperty String sTrimLower Returns Boolean
        If (Left(sTrimLower, 4) <> "set ") Begin
            Function_Return False
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "wrap_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "pscolumnsid") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "child_table_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "item_limit") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "base_item") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "pbcombonavigation") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "move_value_out_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "auto_export_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "auto_index_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "auto_column_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "visible_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "dynamic_update_state") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        Function_Return False
    End_Function

    // Returns True when sTrimLower is a legacy grid Set property that should be
    // commented out rather than removed, so the programmer retains it as a hint.
    //   Set Main_File - tells the programmer which DDO to wire up on the new grid.
    Function IsCommentOutGridProperty String sTrimLower Returns Boolean
        If (Left(sTrimLower, 4) <> "set ") Begin
            Function_Return False
        End
        If (sTrimLower contains "main_file") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        Function_Return False
    End_Function

    // Returns the line with its indentation preserved but content prefixed with "// ".
    // Example: "    Set Main_File to Orders" -> "    // Set Main_File to Orders"
    Function CommentOutLine String sLine Returns String
        String sIndent sTrim
        Move (Trim(sLine)) to sTrim
        Move (Left(sLine, (Length(sLine) - Length(sTrim)))) to sIndent
        Function_Return (sIndent + "// " + sTrim)
    End_Function

    // Extracts the method name (second word) from a trimmed-lowercase procedure or
    // function declaration line.  Returns "" when the line is not a declaration.
    Function ParseProcFuncName String sTrimLower Returns String
        Integer iStart iSpace
        String  sRest

        If (Left(sTrimLower, 10) = "procedure ") Begin
            Move 11 to iStart
        End
        Else If (Left(sTrimLower, 9) = "function ") Begin
            Move 10 to iStart
        End
        Else Begin
            Function_Return ""
        End
        Move (Trim(Mid(sTrimLower, CI_EOL, iStart))) to sRest
        Move (Pos(CS_S, sRest)) to iSpace
        If (iSpace > 0) Begin
            Function_Return (Left(sRest, iSpace - 1))
        End
        Function_Return sRest
    End_Function

    // Case-insensitive replacement of sOldLower (already lowercase) with sNewName
    // in sLine.  Finds the first occurrence only.
    Function ReplaceMethodName String sLine String sOldLower String sNewName Returns String
        Integer iPos iLen
        String  sLower

        Move (Lowercase(sLine)) to sLower
        Move (Pos(sOldLower, sLower)) to iPos
        If (iPos = 0) Begin
            Function_Return sLine
        End
        Move (Length(sOldLower)) to iLen
        Function_Return (Left(sLine, iPos - 1) + sNewName + Mid(sLine, CI_EOL, iPos + iLen))
    End_Function

    // Returns the cDbCJGrid replacement name for a legacy grid method that has a
    // clean 1-to-1 rename, or "" when the method is not in the rename list.
    Function RenameGridMethod String sMethodLower Returns String
        If (sMethodLower = "goto_top_row") Begin
            Function_Return "MoveToFirstRow"
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "goto_bottom_row") Begin
            Function_Return "MoveToLastRow"
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "up_row") Begin
            Function_Return "MoveUpRow"
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "down_row") Begin
            Function_Return "MoveDownRow"
        End
        // Self-rename: preserves the procedure name as-is but routes the body
        // through bInRenameProcedure so it is emitted unchanged by the base class
        // (bypassing subclass transformations such as the bare-Send comment-out rule).
        If (sMethodLower = "activating") Begin
            Function_Return "Activating"
        End
        Function_Return ""
    End_Function

    // Returns True when sMethodLower is a legacy grid method that does not exist
    // in cCJGrid (or whose behaviour differs enough that it must be reviewed).
    // The four clean-rename methods are NOT included here.
    Function IsLegacyOnlyGridMethod String sMethodLower Returns Boolean
        If (sMethodLower = "beginning_of_data") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "end_of_data") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "checkbox_item") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "reorder_list") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "auto_reorder_list") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "scroll") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "clear_current_record") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "col_index") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "display") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "docheckdisplayablerows") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "dotogglecolumnordering") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "fill_list") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "find_current_buffer") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "find_init") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "find_record") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "find_rowid") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "readbyrowid") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "read_by_recnum") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "refresh_page") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "request_new_index") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "serverorderingoverride") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "move_to_column") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "activate_column") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "activate_item") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "doadjustgridwidths") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "column_combo_add_item") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "column_combo_delete_data") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "column_combo_delete_item") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "column_combo_find") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "column_combo_item_count") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "column_combo_refresh") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "column_combo_value") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "domakecolumnvisible") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "request_superfind") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "superfind") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "superfind_next") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "superfind_previous") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "validate_items") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "exec_entry") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "exec_exit") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "exec_validate") Begin
            Function_Return True
        End
        If (sMethodLower = "change_row_color") Begin
